# MENU ITEM WIRING BLUEPRINT — How to Add New Menu Items, Packages & Station Pickers

This document explains the **complete end-to-end pattern** for wiring menu items into the foodwerx intake system. It covers two proven patterns:

1. **Delivery Packages** (e.g. Nicholas Continental) — shadow menu system
2. **Full-Service Stations** (e.g. Viva La Pasta) — station preset system

Any AI assistant should be able to follow this blueprint to add new items to either system.

---

## CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE RULE

There are **TWO separate menu item tables** that must stay in sync:

| Table | ID | Purpose |
|-------|-----|---------|
| **Menu_Lab** | `tbl6gXRT2FPpTdf0J` | Source of truth for **picker filtering** (has `Menu Section`, `Display Type`, `Execution Type` fields) |
| **Legacy Menu Items** | `tbl0aN33DGG6R1sPZ` | Source of truth for **Events linked records** (all Events table linked record fields point here) |

**Both tables must have matching records by name.** The picker queries Menu_Lab for filtering, but resolves the item's name to its legacy table record ID before saving to the Events table.

### Key Field IDs

**Menu_Lab (`tbl6gXRT2FPpTdf0J`):**
- Item Name: `fldpbzDFSg9sYeexU`
- Child Items: `fldDDfLJTI6BK1zKd` (linked records within Menu_Lab)
- Parent Item: `fldLrxghm3bUg0bCx`
- Display Type: `flddOn21WHp7XEaP9` (multi-select)
- Execution Type: `fldnP7tCisqdDkaOI` (multi-select)
- Menu Section: `fld8Okh1qBnMeHwIN` (multi-select — used for delivery intake grouping)
- Test Status: `fldpLvIaTNhtVNeF1` (NOT used in picker formulas)

**Legacy Menu Items (`tbl0aN33DGG6R1sPZ`):**
- Item Name: `fldW5gfSlHRTl01v1`
- Child Items: `fldIu6qmlUwAEn2W9`
- Parent Item: `fldBzB941q8TDeqm3`
- Description: `fldtN2hxy9TS559Rm`
- Dietary Tags: `fldUSr1QgzP4nv9vs`
- Sauces: `fldCUjK7oBckAuNNa`

