## QUICK REFERENCE: Adding a menu section to delivery intake

1. Ensure items in Menu_Lab have the correct `Menu Section` tag
2. Ensure matching items exist in Legacy Menu Items table (same name)
3. Add the tag to `DELIVERY_INTAKE_SECTIONS` in `menuCatalogConfig.ts` if not already there
4. Ensure `Execution Type` maps to a BEO section in `routeTargetFieldFromExecutionTokens()`
5. Test: click the header button → verify items appear in picker → pick one → verify it shows in food list and on BEO print

## QUICK REFERENCE: Adding a station to full-service intake

1. Create components in Station Components table with correct Component Type
2. Create options in Station Options table with selection limits
3. Create/update preset in Station Presets table, linking components and options
4. If custom UI needed: add config in `stationPresets.ts`, mapping in `stationItemMapping.ts`
5. Station type must be in `STATION_TYPE_OPTIONS` in `stations.ts`
6. Test: select station type → verify modal shows grouped components → verify pick limits enforce → verify BEO print
